EP  - 654
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - The article of Cao, Coval, and Hirshleifer (hereafter CCH) presents a stylized model of security trading able to explain some of the features of stock returns, such as (i) positive (negative) skewness after rundowns (run-ups); (ii) volatility clustering; and (iii) large changes in prices with no apparent information arrival. In this discussion I first outline the basic mechanism of the model (Section 1) and then discuss its assumptions and conclusions (Sections 2 and 3), also in light of competing theories. Final remarks are contained in Section 4.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/15.2.649
